			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				This is what I posted on Innoruuk.Com, concerning the &quot;banning&quot; of that story:  <br>  <br> The story supposedly involved roleplaying drama of the raping and mutilation of a 14 yr old girl. <br>  <br> I agree that it's the government's role to look into the situation, to see if the writer is seriously sick in the head that he fantasizes about that, but it's too frightful of a situation to turn away from. We all have disturbed thoughts, driving off a bridge/into oncoming traffic, leaping off a ledge of a tall building.. more in morbid fascination than anything. But those dark thoughts we don't dwell on, and we certainly don't over-fantasize about them, and we certainly don't write stories about someone we like to &quot;roleplay&quot; doing those types of things. <br>  <br> The founder of DragonCon (a local game/fantasy convention), Ed Kramer, was arrested not too long ago (a month ago?) for sexually molesting underraged boys. I'm not saying he's guilty, but I've known this guy through friends and from BBS's long ago (more than 8-10 years). There were always rumors that he liked to pick up young boys/guys, but I thought it was all b.s. Guess it wasn't. =( <br>  <br> Thing is, yes.. it's a hard decision between free speech and possible over-glorification of something too horrible to imagine.  <br>  <br> Honestly, I hoped the guy who wrote the &quot;roleplay story&quot; is brought in by the police and thoroughly questioned about his lifestyle and past. There's things said to promote shock value, but this guy wrote a fantasizing story of one of his characters doing something that evil. Imagine if he was writing that about your sister, or your daughter. <br>  <br> Anyway, I'm not sure if Verant was &quot;right&quot; in their banning, but I support them morally. I'd rather EverQuest/Verant be a place where the company itself won't accept people who get their jollies off writing about raping young children. That, I will respect. And I hate to say it, but I will ban anyone from this page (Innoruuk.Com) who writes a story like that. It's because I will draw a line between representation and free speech, and the depiction and glorification of sexual brutality. <br>  <br> And morally, I think there's a difference between depicting sexual violence in a scientific research/depiction, and describing it like it's some &quot;cool storyline&quot; to your character. <br>  <br>  <br> Cymric <br> Innoruuk.Com <br> <p>

							

