				Hm.. I thought Verant was inspired by MUDs? Many muds out there have torture elements like Dart said and probably some even have minor rape issues. Vikings mainly did raping &amp; pillaging on towns and I've seen muds based on Vikings; is that morally wrong? In Dragonrealms(mud made by same company as Gemstone3) one tactic I used and some others was to weaken an enemy to the point where it's suffering and can't even escape then hide and rest up while the mob slowly dies. That is torture to some degree. In EQ, Root &amp; Damage over Time; Torture. I never read that guy's story but I'm betting it was very descriptive based on the posts here. MUDs were very similar and people actually enjoyed the descriptions to help their imagination. The descriptions this guy gave were probably context enhancements to help set the mood of the scene. Perhaps his character(or another?) had a very horrible past as it sounds, and he wanted to make you realize how horrible it was. Maybe at the time of the writing he was depressed. Dunno =\ I just think that Verant's actions were a little too extreme, especially when it wasn't even on their own site. <p>

							

